@startuml
title Viaverse Worker Onboarding — Activity Diagram
start
:Tap Enable Work Mode;
:Check account eligibility\nstatus + bans + required consent;
if (Allowed?) then (yes)
  :Create worker profile\nname / bio / service intro;
  :Select categories\nskills / subcategories;
  :Set service area\nradius / districts;
  :Set availability\nworking days / hours;
  if (Add portfolio media?) then (yes)
    :Upload portfolio media\nvia media-service;
  endif
  if (Verification required?) then (yes)
    :Submit verification\nidentity/docs if needed;
    :Wait for approval;
  endif
  :Publish worker profile;
  :Emit WorkerProfileActivated;
  :Index worker profile;
  :Opportunity queue ready;
else (no)
  :Show reason and support path;
endif
stop

note bottom
Onboarding should feel lightweight.
Verification may be category/risk dependent,
not mandatory for every low-risk category at launch.
end note
@enduml
